eya_def_tools.data_models.dataset.Dataset
Collection of labelled data for one specific quantity.
The data is labelled by specifying dimensions and including coordinates along the dimensions for each data value.
Attributes: label (Optional[str]): Optional label of the dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. assessment_period (Optional[AssessmentPeriod(StrEnum)]): Optional period of or in time that has been assessed and for which the dataset is applicable. This field is to be included only when relevant. Default is None. dimensions (Optional[list[DatasetDimension(StrEnum)]]): Dimensions along which the dataset is binned. All statistics within the same dataset object must have the same dimensions. The dimensions must correspond to and be listed in the same order as the coordinates for the values of all statistics. A dataset without dimensions can only have a single value for each statistic. Default is None. statistics (list[DatasetStatistic]): List of dataset statistic objects that each include data values for a specific statistic type. For example, there may be two statistics, one for mean values and one for standard deviation values.

eya_def_tools.data_models.dataset.DatasetStatistic
Dataset values for one specific statistic type.
Attributes: description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the dataset statistic, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the dataset statistic, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. statistic_type (UnionType[BasicStatisticType(StrEnum), ExceedanceLevelStatisticType]): Type of statistic that the component of the dataset contains. All values must correspond to this statistic. It can be either the string identifier of a basic statistic type (e.g. 'mean') or a specification of a probability of exceedance level. values (Union[float, list[tuple[list[Union[int, float, str]], float]]]): Dataset value(s) as a single number or one or more values at coordinates. If more than one value is included the values must be represented together with coordinates. A single value can be included either with or without coordinates. The coordinates must correspond to and be listed the same order as the dimensions specified for the dataset.

eya_def_tools.data_models.dataset.ExceedanceLevelStatisticType
Probability of exceedance level statistic type.
Attributes: exceedance_level (float): The dimensionless probability of exceedance level (i.e. probability value between 0.0 and 1.0) of the statistic.

eya_def_tools.data_models.energy_assessment.EnergyAssessment

Attributes: gross_energy_assessment (GrossEnergyAssessment): Details and results for the assessment of gross energy yield. plant_performance_assessment (PlantPerformanceAssessment): Plant performance loss assessment categories including results. net_energy_assessment (NetEnergyAssessment): Details and results for the assessment of net energy yield.

eya_def_tools.data_models.energy_assessment.GrossEnergyAssessment

Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the gross energy assessment, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. results (EnergyAssessmentResults): Gross EYA estimates.

eya_def_tools.data_models.energy_assessment.NetEnergyAssessment
Net energy assessment details and results.
Attributes: description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the net energy assessment, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the net energy assessment, which should not be empty if the field is included. eya_def_tools.data_models.plant_performance.PlantPerformanceAssessment
Plant performance loss assessment broken into categories.
Attributes: categories (list[PlantPerformanceCategory]): Plant performance loss assessment categories including results. results (PlantPerformanceResults): Overall plant performance loss assessment results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.energy_assessment.EnergyAssessmentResults
Energy assessment results.
Attributes: annual_energy_production (list[Dataset]): Annual energy production (AEP) estimates at the turbine location(s) in gigawatt hour (GW h). The dimension of the first standard result dataset should be 'wind_farm_id'. The dimension of the second standard result dataset should be 'turbine_id'. Further results with other dimensions may be included optionally.

eya_def_tools.data_models.plant_performance.PlantPerformanceCategory
Plant performance loss assessment category.
Attributes: label (PlantPerformanceCategoryLabel(StrEnum)): Label of the plant performance loss category. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the plant performance loss category, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the plant performance loss category, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. subcategories (list[PlantPerformanceSubcategory]): Plant performance loss assessment subcategories that fall under the category. The subcategory objects include details and results at the subcategory level. results (PlantPerformanceResults): Plant performance assessment category results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.plant_performance.PlantPerformanceResults
Plant performance loss assessment results.
Attributes: efficiency (list[Dataset]): Dimensionless plant performance efficiency (loss factor) results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.plant_performance.PlantPerformanceSubcategory
Plant performance loss assessment subcategory.
Attributes: label (PlantPerformanceSubcategoryLabel(StrEnum)): Label of the plant performance loss subcategory. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the plant performance loss subcategory, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the plant performance loss subcategory, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. basis (AssessmentBasis(StrEnum)): Basis of plant performance loss subcategory assessment. The basis describes the level of detail of the calculation or estimate used in the assessment of the subcategory. variability (TimeVariabilityType(StrEnum)): Considered variability in the plant performance loss subcategory. elements (Optional[list[PlantPerformanceSubcategoryElement]]): Optional plant performance loss assessment elements that fall under the subcategory. The element objects include details and results at the element level. A breakdown of plant performance loss subcategories into elements is optional and can be included only for a subset of the subcategories, as relevant. Whereas the categories and subcategories are fixed, the user may freely define element labels. Default is None. results (PlantPerformanceResults): Plant performance assessment subcategory results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.plant_performance.PlantPerformanceSubcategoryElement
Plant performance loss assessment subcategory element.
Attributes: label (str): Label of the plant performance loss subcategory element. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the plant performance loss subcategory element, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the plant performance loss subcategory element, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. basis (AssessmentBasis(StrEnum)): Basis of plant performance loss subcategory element assessment. The basis describes the level of detail of the calculation or estimate used in the assessment of the element. variability (TimeVariabilityType(StrEnum)): Considered variability in the plant performance loss subcategory element. is_independent (bool): Whether the plant performance loss subcategory element is independent of all other elements. Default is True. results (PlantPerformanceResults): Plant performance assessment subcategory element results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.scenario.Scenario
Single unique energy yield assessment scenario.
Attributes: id (Optional[str]): Optional unique identifier of the scenario, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. label (str): Label of the scenario. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the scenario, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the scenario, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. is_main_scenario (Optional[bool]): Optional flag to specify whether or not it is the main scenario in the report. Default is None. wind_farm_ids (list[str]): List of the IDs for all wind farms included in the scenario. Each ID refers to a wind farm configuration data object within the 'wind_farms' section of the top-level of the EYA DEF document. Only wind farms for which turbine interaction effects are modelled shall be included. turbine_wind_resource_assessment (TurbineWindResourceAssessment): Wind resource assessment at the turbine locations. energy_assessment (EnergyAssessment): Energy assessment details and results, including gross energy, plant performance, net energy and uncertainties.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_resource.TurbineWindResourceAssessment
Wind resource assessment at the turbine locations.
Attributes: wind_resource_assessment_id_reference (str): The ID of the wind resource assessment on which the turbine wind resource assessment is based. This must refer to an ID of a wind resource assessment included at the top level of the EYA DEF. The schema requires that a turbine wind resource assessment is based on only one wind resource assessment. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the turbine wind resource assessment, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the turbine wind resource assessment, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. results (TurbineWindResourceResults): Results of the wind resource assessment at the turbine location(s). wind_uncertainty_assessment (WindUncertaintyAssessment): Wind related uncertainty assessment categories including results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_resource.TurbineWindResourceResults
Wind resource assessment results at turbine locations.
Attributes: wind_speed (list[Dataset]): Final long-term wind speed estimates at the turbine location(s) at hub height in metre per second (m s-1). The dimension of the first standard result dataset should be 'turbine_id'. Further results with other dimensions may be included optionally. probability (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final long-term probability distribution estimates at the turbine location(s) at hub height, as dimensionless values. The first standard result dataset should comprise the joint wind speed and direction probability distributions, with dimensions 'turbine_id', 'wind_speed' and 'wind_from_direction' (in that order). The wind speed coordinates should be 1.0 metre per second bins centered on whole numbers, with the first bin half the width (i.e. 0.25, 1.0, 2.0, 3.0, ...). The wind direction coordinates should be twelve 30.0 degree bins, with the the first bin centered at 0.0. Further results with other dimensions may also be included. Default is None. ambient_turbulence_intensity (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final ambient turbulence intensity estimates at the turbine location(s) at hub height, as dimensionless values. The first standard result dataset should comprise the ambient turbulence intensity as a function of wind speed, with the dimensions 'turbine_id' and 'wind_speed' (in that order). The wind speed coordinates should be 1.0 metre per second bins centered on whole numbers, with the first bin half the width (i.e. 0.25, 1.0, 2.0, 3.0, ...). Further results with other dimensions may also be included. Default is None. wind_shear_exponent (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final power law wind shear exponent estimates at the turbine location(s). The dimension of the first standard result dataset should be 'turbine_id'. Further results with other dimensions may also be included. Default is None. temperature (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final long-term temperature estimates at the turbine location(s) at hub height in degree C. The dimension of the first standard result dataset should be 'turbine_id'. Further results with other dimensions may also be included. Default is None. air_density (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Final long-term air density estimates at the turbine location(s) at hub height in kilogram per cubic metre (kg m-3). The dimension of the first standard result dataset should be 'turbine_id'. Further results with other dimensions may also be included. Default is None. displacement_height (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Estimated effective displacement of the boundary layer at the turbine location(s) due to vegetation (forestry) in metre. The displacement height is measured as positive upwards from the ground level. This field is optional as it is only relevant at forested sites. The dimension of the first standard result dataset should be 'turbine_id'. Further results with other dimensions, such as displacement height binned by wind direction, may also be included. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_uncertainty.WindUncertaintyAssessment
Wind related uncertainty assessment broken into categories.
Attributes: categories (list[WindUncertaintyCategory]): Wind related uncertainty assessment categories including results. results (UncertaintyResults): Overall wind related uncertainty assessment results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_uncertainty.UncertaintyResults
Uncertainty assessment results.
Attributes: relative_wind_speed_uncertainty (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Uncertainty assessment results as dimensionless relative values expressed in terms of wind speed and calculated as the standard deviation of the wind speed uncertainty distribution divided by the mean wind speed. Default is None. relative_energy_uncertainty (Optional[list[Dataset]]): Uncertainty assessment results as dimensionless relative values expressed in terms of AEP (annual energy production) and calculated as the standard deviation of the energy uncertainty distribution divided by the net P50 (50% probability of exceedance level) AEP. Default is None.

Default is None. subcategories (list[WindUncertaintySubcategory]): Wind related uncertainty assessment subcategories that fall under the category. eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_uncertainty.WindUncertaintySubcategory
